\begin_layout Section
Partition functions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\emph on
Recall
\emph default
: The microcanonical partition function 
\begin_inset Formula $\Omega\left(E,x\right)$
\end_inset

 defines the equilibrium state given by the energy 
\begin_inset Formula $E$
\end_inset

 of a closed system via the relation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:microcanonical-partition-function"

\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
P_{r}\left(E,x\right) & =\begin{cases}
\frac{1}{\Omega\left(E,x\right)} & E-\delta E\le E_{r}\le E\\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

The ensemble with such a probability is called 
\emph on
microcanonical
\emph default
.
\end_layout

