\begin_inset Formula $\KET{\nu}$
\end_inset

 appears in the set 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ \KET{\nu_{1}},\ldots,\KET{\nu_{N}}\right\} $
\end_inset

.
 It holds:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
n_{\nu} & \in\left\{ 0,1\right\}  &  & \text{fermions}\\
n_{\nu} & \in\left\{ 0,1,\ldots,N\right\}  &  & \text{bosons}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

