\begin_layout Standard
Not all components entering entering 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:GeneralHamiltonian"

\end_inset

 have to be treated simultaneously.
 The motion of the electrons and the motion of the ions decouple.
 (Born-Oppenheimer approximation)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The decoupling is based on the observation that, due to their large mass
 
\begin_inset Formula $M_{\alpha}$
\end_inset

, the ions move much slower than the electrons of mass 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

, i.e.
 the electrons adapt instantaneously to the actual ion configuration.
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\frac{m}{M_{\alpha}} & \approx10^{-4}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
