\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Assume that the whole system is in thermal equilibrium.
 So the electrons and the ions have the same average thermal energy per
 degree of freedom.
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\left\langle \frac{mv_{i}^{2}}{2}\right\rangle  & =\left\langle \frac{M_{\alpha}v_{\alpha}^{2}}{2}\right\rangle =\frac{k_{B}T}{2}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

Due to 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{m}{M_{\alpha}}\approx10^{-4}$
\end_inset

 the electrons move faster.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
