\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order to describe the solid, we should solve the Schrödinger equation:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\hat{H}\psi & =E\psi
\end{align*}

\end_inset

Here 
\begin_inset Formula $\psi=\psi\left(\left(\vec{r}_{j}\right),\left(\vec{R}_{\alpha}\right)\right)=:\psi\left(\vec{r},\vec{R}\right)$
\end_inset

 depends on the positions of the electrons and the ions.
\end_layout

