\begin_layout Enumerate
Introduce a set of operators 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{a}_{\lambda}$
\end_inset

 and their adjoints 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{a}_{\lambda}^{\dagger}$
\end_inset

 such that holds:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\hat{a}_{\lambda}\KET 0 & =0\\
\mathcal{N}\prod_{i=1}^{N}\hat{a}_{\lambda_{\nu_{i}}}^{\dagger}\KET 0 & =\mathcal{N}\hat{a}_{\lambda_{\nu_{1}}}^{\dagger}\cdot\ldots\cdot\hat{a}_{\lambda_{\nu_{N}}}^{\dagger}\KET 0:=\KET{\lambda_{\nu_{1}},\ldots,\lambda_{\nu_{n}}}
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{N}$
\end_inset

 is a normalization factor with
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\mathcal{N}^{-1} & =\sqrt{\prod_{\lambda}n_{\lambda}}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

and 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{\lambda}$
\end_inset

 is the number of times the state 
\begin_inset Formula $\KET{\lambda}$
\end_inset

 appears in the family 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\KET{\lambda_{\nu_{1}}},\ldots,\KET{\lambda_{\nu_{N}}}\right)$
\end_inset

.
 It holds 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{\lambda}\in\mathbb{N}$
\end_inset

 for bosons and 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{\lambda}\in\left\{ 0,1\right\} $
\end_inset

 for fermions.
 As we shall proof holds
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\KET{\lambda_{\nu_{1}},\ldots,\lambda_{\nu_{N}}} & =\KET{n_{\lambda_{1}},n_{\lambda_{2}},\ldots}\label{eq:occupation-number-representation}
\end{align}

\end_inset

as in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:Number-KET"

\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
In order to care for the symmetry of the so constructed states, 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{a}_{\lambda}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{a}_{\lambda}^{\dagger}$
\end_inset

 have to fulfill the following commutation relations:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align}
\left[\hat{a}_{\lambda},\hat{a}_{\mu}^{\dagger}\right]_{\xi} & :=\hat{a}_{\lambda}\hat{a}_{\mu}^{\dagger}+\xi\hat{a}_{\mu}^{\dagger}\hat{a}_{\lambda}=\delta_{\mu\nu}\label{eq:commutation-relation1}\\
\left[\hat{a}_{\lambda},\hat{a}_{\mu}\right]_{\xi} & =\left[\hat{a}_{\lambda}^{\dagger},\hat{a}_{\mu}^{\dagger}\right]_{\xi}=0\label{eq:commutation-relation2}
\end{align}

\end_inset

To understand 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:commutation-relation2"

\end_inset

 observe:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\KET{\lambda,\mu} & =\mathcal{N}\hat{a}_{\lambda}^{\dagger}\hat{a}_{\mu}^{\dagger}\KET 0\\
\KET{\mu,\lambda} & =\mathcal{N}\hat{a}_{\mu}^{\dagger}\hat{a}_{\lambda}^{\dagger}\KET 0\stackrel{\eqref{eq:commutation-relation2}}{=}-\xi\KET{\lambda,\mu}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

These are the proper symmetry relations.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

On the other hand 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:commutation-relation1"

\end_inset

 ensures orthonormality:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\delta_{\lambda\mu} & =\BraKet{0|\hat{a}_{\lambda}\hat{a}_{\mu}^{\dagger}|0}=\BraKet{0|\left(-\xi\right)\hat{a}_{\mu}^{\dagger}\hat{a}_{\lambda}+\left[\hat{a}_{\lambda},\hat{a}_{\mu}^{\dagger}\right]_{\xi}|0}=\\
 & =\underbrace{\BraKet{0|\left(-\xi\right)\hat{a}_{\mu}^{\dagger}\hat{a}_{\lambda}|0}}_{=0}+\BraKet{0|\left[\hat{a}_{\lambda},\hat{a}_{\mu}^{\dagger}\right]_{\xi}|0}=\BraKet{0|\left[\hat{a}_{\lambda},\hat{a}_{\mu}^{\dagger}\right]_{\xi}|0}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

Under the prescriptions i) - iii), 
\emph on
any
\emph default
 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

-body state can be generated by the application of a set of 
\begin_inset Formula $N$
\end_inset

 independent creation operators 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{a}_{\lambda}^{\dagger}$
\end_inset

 to a vacuum state.
 This is the completeness of the second quantization approach.
\end_layout

