\begin_inset Formula $\KET{\lambda_{\nu_{1}},\lambda_{\nu_{2}},\ldots,\lambda_{\nu_{N}}}$
\end_inset

.
 The space
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\mathcal{F} & =\bigoplus_{N=0}^{\infty}\mathcal{F}_{N}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

containing 
\emph on
all
\emph default
 many-body states is called 
\emph on
Fock space
\emph default
.
 While the operator algebra of 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{a}_{\lambda}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{a}_{\lambda}^{\dagger}$
\end_inset

 does not close in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{F}_{N}$
\end_inset

, it does in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{F}$
\end_inset

.
