\begin_layout Enumerate
Define the occupation number operator:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\hat{n}_{\lambda} & =\hat{a}_{\lambda}^{\dagger}\hat{a}_{\lambda}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

For it holds:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\hat{n}_{\lambda}\left(\hat{a}_{\lambda}^{\dagger}\right)^{n_{\lambda}}\KET 0 & =n_{\lambda}\left(\hat{a}_{\lambda}^{\dagger}\right)^{n_{\lambda}}\KET 0
\end{align*}

\end_inset

This means that 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(\hat{a}_{\lambda}^{\dagger}\right)^{n_{\lambda}}\KET 0$
\end_inset

 is an eigenstate of 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{n}_{\lambda}$
\end_inset

 with eigenvalue 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{\lambda}$
\end_inset

.
 Moreover we have:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\hat{n}_{\lambda}\KET{\lambda_{\nu_{1}},\ldots,\lambda_{\nu_{N}}} & =\mathcal{N}\hat{a}_{\lambda}^{\dagger}\hat{a}_{\lambda}\prod_{i=1}^{N}\hat{a}_{\lambda_{\nu_{i}}}^{\dagger}\KET 0=\sum_{i=1}^{N}\delta_{\lambda\lambda_{\nu_{i}}}\KET{\lambda_{\nu_{1}},\ldots,\lambda_{\nu_{N}}}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

So 
\begin_inset Formula $\KET{\lambda_{\nu_{1}},\ldots,\lambda_{\nu_{N}}}$
\end_inset

 is an eigenstate of 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{n}_{\lambda}$
\end_inset

 with eigenvalue 
\begin_inset Formula $n_{\lambda}$
\end_inset

, which proofs the equality 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:occupation-number-representation"

\end_inset

.
