\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The linear response theory is based on the idea that the response of a system
 to a weak perturbation, proportional to the perturbation itself, can be
 calculated to the 
\emph on
lowest
\emph default
 order in the perturbation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
